env_package_full: {'type': 'soil', 'name': 'Rock Bay: soil', 'id': 'mge98655', 'data': {'ph': 'pH was maintained between 6 and 8 during fermentation, used a BioFlo reactor', 'previous_land_use': 'Tannery, sawmills, coal gasification plant, propane tank farm, concrete batch plant, asphalt plant, gas stations, gravel shipping, marine transportation', 'water_content_soil_meth': 'Dried soil was mixed with sterile milliQ water in laboratory conditions prior to fermentation', 'store_cond': '-80 degrees glycerol stock, stored for ~4 years', 'extreme_event': 'Highly contaminated environment with hydrocarbons and heavy metals, veins of coal tar were visible to the naked eye, and samples smelled strongly of oil', 'previous_land_use_meth': 'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rock_Bay,_Victoria, http://www.tbs-sct.gc.ca/dfrp-rbif/pn-nb/17348-eng.aspx', 'ph_meth': 'pH probes', 'env_package': 'soil', 'water_content_soil': '80g/100g in fermentation mix', 'cur_land_use': 'Harbor/bay area, marine transportation', 'annual_season_temp': '10.3', 'sieving': 'Before fermentation, soil was homogenized and sieved for <1 cm diameter particles', 'sample_name': 'Rock Bay', 'samp_weight_dna_ext': '1 kg', 'pool_dna_extracts': '10 samples of the fermentation slurry were combined for a total of 3 g soil (5 time points during fermentation, in duplicate) and extracted once with MoBio kit', 'annual_season_precpt': '607.6'}}
